      <div class="msgContentFrame"><div class="msgQuote"><div class="source">KujaKoF wrote:</div><div class="orig">Lets get these class boards going.</div></div> <br /> <br />It wasn't going before?  <img border="0" src="http://common.zam.com/shared/smilies/confused.gif" alt="Smiley: confused"/> <br /> <br />I'm going to be lazy, and repost my build ideas from before.  In my limited experience with the beta, I haven't seen anything yet to make me reconsider them.  I'm looking forward to actually getting a chance to take the class further and experiment with them, though. <br /> <br /><div class="msgQuote"><div class="source">Quote:</div><div class="orig">So the common themes that I'm seeing involve controlling/increasing/expending HP and TP. I'm trying to figure out what sort of roles Lancer might naturally fall into using such abilities. I get the impression of Lancer naturally existing as a sort of hybrid DRK/SAM that is constantly expending HP in order to bolster attack power or increase TP, then absorbing it back again with Life Surge. Then tack on the Collusion ability for some minor hate control. <br /> <br />I see an ability in the Marauder line that seem to gel with that theme: <br /> <br />Bloodbath: Revel in the blood of an enemy, converting a percetage of the damage dealt by your next successful attack into HP. <br /> <br />Other than that, I'm hard-pressed to find other DoW abilities that really bolster what appear to me to be Lancer's natural strengths. Granted, there are probably quite a few aspects of the armory system that I'm either not grasping properly, or aren't yet public knowledge. <br /> <br />Myself, I intend to be doing a decent amount of solo/duo-ing. I'm liking the idea of combining some Conjurer and Thaumaturge abilities with Lancer in order to facilitate that. <br /> <br />Drain: Transfers HP from enemies within area of effect to you. <br />Sacrifice: Consumes HP to restore a portion of the target's HP. <br />Siphon TP: Transfers TP from the target to you. <br /> <br />These abilities, plus some assorted Cure/Protect sort of spells, seem to lend themselves pretty well towards a solo/duo Lancer, as far as I can tell. <br /> <br /></div></div> <br /> <br /><i><span class="sm">Edited, Aug 30th 2010  5:22pm by Eske </span></i><div class="msgSig"><div class="msgSigBar sm">----------------------------</div><span class="sm">Eske Eir <br />Server: Selbina <br />Linkshell: Einherjar <br />Recruitment Thread can be found <a href="HTTP://ffxiv.zam.com/forum.html?forum=209&amp;mid=128383173532179182&amp;page=1" rel="external" title="ffxiv.zam.com/forum.html?forum=209&amp;mid=128383173532179182&amp;page=1">here</a>.</span></div></div>
