      <div class="msgContentFrame"><div class="msgQuote"><div class="source">volta1 wrote:</div><div class="orig"><div class="msgQuote"><div class="source">elmoreb wrote:</div><div class="orig">And no leg sweep? Leg sweep is awesome.  <br /> <br />Im currently 22 with the following <br /> <br />78 str <br />63 vit <br />15 dex <br /> <br /> <br />Light thrust <br />Feint <br />Doomspike <br />Leg Sweep <br />Pierce <br />Life Surge <br />Comrade in arms ( mostly because its a skill up chance without damage) <br />shock spikes <br />invigorate <br />Bloodbath ( rarely used, but helps sometimes) <br /> <br /> <br />I keep tranquility on bar 2. When I need mana, I switch to conj, use tranquility, then switch back.  <br /> <br />In the future I plan on getting quickstep from archery and thats about all from non-lancer skills. </div></div> <br /> <br />I mean this sincerely - aren't both your STR and VIT capped at your rank?  And why is your DEX so low?  Do you just plan on missing, Feinting, and repeating?  Honestly, how good (or bad) is your hit ratio? <br /> <br />I'm rolling with about 65 STR, 60DEX, 60VIT and ~35MND (magic def) at R20 and L29.  My hit ratio is pretty good, I do solid damage, and I also have CONJ8 so I usually have Cure equipped on my bar.</div></div> <br /> <br />My physical level is only 25. So no vit isnt maxed. Str is maxed though. Cap is 32+(level*2) or 76 at 22. Im 23 now though.  <br /> <br />My hit ratio on green/yellow mobs is about 75% ( over 200 hits) with no +acc gear on. I took off the gear for some testing, which is why I know that number in the first place. This includes both evade and misses with no life surge on. Obviously I hit more often with my brass rings and life surge on.   <br /> <br />Dex is over-rated for accuracy. Since dropping it from 60, I have not noticed a difference. I am not sure wether dex is worthwhile for the crit. It may be. Im pretty unimpressed with crit damage though. <br /> <br />I have found no use for cure 1 on any mob that requires me to heal, but I have base mnd. Over the course of casting cure, I do no damage, get hit for 120, and miss out on 2 hits ( 40-50 hp), meaning I break even or only gain a slight benefit. Might be different with higher mind or cure 2.  <br /> <br />I can kill any yellow con mob I have seen with ease. Orange mobs are hit or miss. For example I can kill orange puks and squirrels with no risk, but orange Aldgoat Billys or orange bats kill me pretty much every time. I can kill red puks and fat dodos. Red squirrels are doable but risky, and I'm as likely to die as not. So I feel pretty solid. I do think I could be optimized a bit more. Protect and cure 2 might help, and Im tempted to put more into MND and try that out. Defender is something else that I think might be worth trying solo, as well as some other skills here and there. <br /> <br /></div>
